tor.log:2086:./state/artifacts/20260505T161636-endpoint-domain-and-schema/evaluator.log:2193:{\\\"decision\\\":\\\"not_done\\\",\\\"recommend_promotion\\\":false,\\\"confidence\\\":0,\\\"summary\\\":\\\"The repository implementation is within the intended persistence slice, but I found one substantive schema gap against the PRD-backed scope: the PRD create/edit endpoint model includes an optional endpoint `title` and response-case fields such as `priority`, case-level delay, and error mode. The current Prisma schema/docs omit those fields, so the persistence shape does not fully cover the MVP endpoint-management data it is supposed to carry.\\\",\\\"satisfied_exit_criteria\\\":[\\\"`db:prepare` is wired through Prisma migrate/generate/seed and the recorded mandatory gates passed.\\\",\\\"Repeatability is covered by a unit test that runs `db:prepare` twice against an isolated SQLite DB and verifies singular seed rows.\\\",\\\"The implementation includes immutable endpoint IDs, endpoint name/description/enabled/delete code/default response/timestamps, ordered parameters, response cases, and endpoint-level basic failure fields.\\\",\\\"The implementation stays scoped to persistence and does not add UI/runtime/auth feature fronts.\\\"],\\\"missing_requirements\\\":[\\\"Prisma schema and generated docs do not include endpoint `title`, which the PRD lists as part of create/edit endpoint data.\\\",\\\"ResponseCase schema lacks `priority`, `delayMs`, and case-level error fields described by the PRD response-case model; current fields only cover matching JSON, response JSON, status code, and default marker.\\\"],\\\"human_review_triggers\\\":[\\\"Implementation changes may not fully satisfy the PRD-backed persistence shape required before later endpoint validation/UI/runtime tasks.\\\"]}\\nstate/artifacts/20260505T163710-endpoint-domain-and-schema/evaluator.log:1903:./state/artifacts/20260505T162122-endpoint-domain-and-schema/evaluator.log:2087:./state/artifacts/20260505T161